{
  "texts": [
    "Monster's architecture utilizes the Wazuh agent for endpoint monitoring, ELK Stack for data collection, processing, storage and visualization, RabbitMQ for queuing and SearchGuard for encryption and authentication.",
    "The community edition of SIEMonster is free whereas the professional, enterprise and MSSP editions require a subscription ranging from $600 to $5000 per month.",
    "Open-Source Security Information Management (OSSIM) [51] is an open-source variant of the commercially available AlienVault Unified Security Management (USM).",
    "OSSIM provides all the basic SIEM functionalities along with vulnerability scanning and asset discovery.",
    "The downside is that it is limited in terms of event processing speed and built-in correlation rules and lacks a threat intelligence module."
  ]
}